Standard .gitignore for Node/React Full-Stack Applications
###################################
1. Dependency Directories
###################################
Node.js dependencies in the root (if used)
/node_modules
/package-lock.json
Dependencies installed in the client-side
/client/node_modules
Dependencies installed in the server-side
/server/node_modules/
/server/package-lock.json
Yarn PnP files
.pnp
.pnp.js
###################################
2. Build & Temporary Files
###################################
Production build output
/client/dist
/client/build
/build
/dist
/out
Log files
.log
npm-debug.log
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
###################################
3. Development and Backup Files (CRITICAL ADDITIONS)
###################################
Backup files created by various processes
*.orig
*.bak
*.old
Specific files generated during debugging (like your bad DB file)
*.badDB
Local environment variables (CRITICAL: DO NOT COMMIT SECRETS)
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.vscode
.idea
Local database files (if any)
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
/db.json
###################################
4. Operating System Files
###################################
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db